``\r\n\r\nI tested the whole blog tutorial project like this, and everything seemed to work. I'm not sure if simply dropping the plugin load will fix the bug, or if there is some functionality that relies on the plugin that will have to be rewritten.\r\n\r\n#### What is the expected behavior?\r\nPadrino should work correctly with the schema gem.\r\n\r\n#### Which versions of Ruby, Padrino, Sinatra, Rack, OS are you using? Did this work in previous versions?\r\nRuby - 2.4.2\r\nPadrino - 0.14.1.1\r\nSinatra - 2.0\r\nRack - 2.0.3\r\nOS - Elementary OS 0.4.1","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/padrino/padrino-framework/issues/2164","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/padrino/padrino-framework","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/padrino/padrino-framework/issues/2164/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/padrino/padrino-framework/issues/2164/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/padrino/padrino-framework/issues/2164/events","html_url":"https://github.com/padrino/padrino-framework/issues/2164","id":277737155,"number":2164,"title":"padrino gen task doesn't fit latest ruby conventions","user":{"login":"jorgefuertes","id":194590,"avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/194590?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes","html_url":"https://github.com/jorgefuertes","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jorgefuertes/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"h